{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "uvpelt", "icon": "SOP/uvpelt", "tags": "uvs, textures, cleanup", "index": "no", "version": "", "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["UV Pelt"], "extent": [104, 116]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Relaxes UVs by pulling them out toward the edges of the texture area."], "extent": [116, 194]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["UVPelt operates very similar to how a tanner\ncreates a pelt. Cuts are made to the geometry to produce a surface\ntopologically equivalent to a disc. The boundaries of this surface are\nconnected to a frame and stretched out."], "extent": [194, 418]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Any closed face can be used as a frame for the pelt. A circle is used if\nno frame is specified. A hint polygon is used to specify which section\nof the geometry to pelt after performing the cuts. The boundary with an\nedge closest to the hint polygon is the one connected to the frame. The\nframe is parameterized to the range ", {"type": "code", "text": ["[0, 1)"]}, ". The boundary points are\nspaced around the frame at distances in the frame\u2019s parameterization\nthat are proportional to the edge length with the neighboring boundary\npoint."], "extent": [418, 924]}, {"type": "box_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "box", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [16, 22], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The best way to visualize the effects on UVs is in the UV view. To change a viewport to show UVs, click the View menu in the top right corner of a viewport and choose ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Set View \u25b8 UV viewport"]}, ", or move the mouse over the view and press ", {"keys": ["Space", "5"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, "."], "extent": [46, 303]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["You can also visualize UV attribute values in the 3D view using an ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/basics/visualizers", "type": "link", "text": ["attribute visualizer"], "fullpath": "/basics/visualizers"}, "."], "extent": [303, 420]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "visualizePara"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["UVPelt creates the UV texture attribute if it does not already exist.\nThe attribute class (Vertices or Points) is determined by the Target\nType. It is recommended that UVs be applied to vertices, since this\nallows fine control on polygonal geometry and the ability to fix seams\nat the boundary of a texture."], "extent": [964, 1273]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1273, 1279], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["UVPelt only operates on polygons. Other geometry type such as Bezier\n    and NURBS surfaces can be converted to polygons using a Convert\n    operation prior to applying UVPelt."], "extent": [1279, 1461]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 2, "id": "includeme", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Using UV Pelt"], "extent": [439, 471], "body": [{"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SOP/uvpelt", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/uvpelt"}, {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/uvpelt", "type": "link", "text": ["UV Pelt"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/uvpelt"}, " tool on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Texture"]}, " tab."], "extent": [471, 569]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Select the edges that will form the boundary of the pelt."], "extent": [569, 633], "body": [{"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 8, "role": "item", "extent": [633, 646], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["You can easily select loops of edges using the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/edgeloop", "type": "link", "text": ["Edge Loop"], "fullpath": "/shelf/edgeloop"}, " tool."], "extent": [646, 739]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/shelf/uv_pelt_select.jpg", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/uv_pelt_select.jpg"}], "extent": [739, 793]}], "container": true}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Press ", {"keys": ["Enter"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " to unwrap your selection.  "], "extent": [793, 843], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/shelf/uv_pelt_after.jpg", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/uv_pelt_after.jpg"}], "extent": [843, 896]}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["You can scale the pelt by increasing the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Boundary Springs"]}, " in the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/ref/panes/parms", "type": "link", "text": ["parameter editor"], "fullpath": "/ref/panes/parms"}, ". You can also use ", {"scheme": null, "value": "uvedit", "type": "link", "text": ["UV Edit"], "fullpath": "/shelf/uvedit"}, " to move the UVs."], "extent": [896, 1058]}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1496, 1508], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Edge Cut Group"], "extent": [1508, 1528], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Edges to cut."], "extent": [1555, 1577]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/group"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Target Type"], "extent": [1577, 1594], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The attribute class (Vertices or Points) that will receive the\n        UV attributes."], "extent": [1622, 1716]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/target"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Create Output Group"], "extent": [1716, 1741], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Indicates a primitive group should be created for the polygons\n        making up the pelt."], "extent": [1775, 1874]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/outputtoggle"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Output Group"], "extent": [1874, 1892], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Name of the primitive group to create."], "extent": [1925, 1973]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/outputgroup"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 4, "text": ["Pelt"], "extent": [1973, 1988], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 8, "text": ["Iterations"], "extent": [1988, 2009], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["Specifies the number of iterations of the algorithm for\n            solving the UV positions."], "extent": [2040, 2146]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/iters"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 8, "text": ["Boundary Springs"], "extent": [2146, 2172], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["The strength of the springs connecting the pelt boundary to\n            the frame."], "extent": [2199, 2294]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/k"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 8, "text": ["Stiffness Attribute"], "extent": [2294, 2323], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["Specifies an attribute of the input geometry\u2019s points that\n            will be used to scale the strength of the springs connected\n            to the point."], "extent": [2358, 2527]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/stiffness"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 8, "text": ["Hint Primitive"], "extent": [2527, 2551], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["The primitive specifying which section of the geometry forms\n            the pelt."], "extent": [2585, 2681]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/hintprim"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 4, "text": ["Frame"], "extent": [2681, 2697], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 8, "text": ["Frame"], "extent": [2697, 2712], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["The primitive to use for the frame."], "extent": [2743, 2792]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/frame"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 8, "text": ["U From"], "extent": [2792, 2808], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["The attribute of the frame used for the U coordinate."], "extent": [2839, 2905]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/ufrom"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 8, "text": ["V From"], "extent": [2905, 2921], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["The attribute of the frame used for the V coordinate."], "extent": [2952, 3018]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/vfrom"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 8, "text": ["Use Range"], "extent": [3018, 3037], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["Indicates the UV coordinates should be moved to the ranges\n            specified with U Range and V Range."], "extent": [3071, 3190]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/userange"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 8, "text": ["U Range"], "extent": [3190, 3207], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["The location of the left and right edges, respectively, of\n            the texture"], "extent": [3239, 3334]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/urange"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 8, "text": ["V Range"], "extent": [3334, 3351], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["The location of the bottom and top edges, respectively, of\n            the texture"], "extent": [3383, 3478]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/vrange"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 8, "text": ["Orientation"], "extent": [3478, 3499], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["Specifies where on the frame to position the first boundary\n            point (the boundary point closest to the hint polygon)."], "extent": [3536, 3676]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/orientation"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 8, "text": ["Weight Attribute"], "extent": [3676, 3702], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["Specifies an attribute of the frame\u2019s points that will guide\n            the process of connecting boundary points to the frame."], "extent": [3734, 3876]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"channels": "/weight"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [3876, 3885], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/uvproject", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/uvproject"}], "extent": [3885, 3912]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/uvquickshade", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/uvquickshade"}], "extent": [3912, 3942]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/texture", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/texture"}], "extent": [3942, 3967]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/uvunwrap", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/uvunwrap"}], "extent": [3967, 3994]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["UV Pelt"], "summary": ["Relaxes UVs by pulling them out toward the edges of the texture area."], "included": ["/nodes/sop/texture_common", "/shelf/uvpelt"]}